The paper deals with problems related to geometry and combinatorics, specifically incidences between lines and points in three dimensions. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algebraic techniques, which suggests cs.AG (Algebraic Geometry) as a possible sub-category. The use of bounds and complexity analysis suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves some results related to symplectic geometry, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
